Sheet1.Title: Asia's first metaverse wedding portrait
Sheet1.Description:
This NFT featuring the first meta-verse wedding of Asia is one of the most exclusive NFT brought to you by Namastey-NFT.
 This NFT is about the attire that the bride and the groom chose for themselves. The groom is attired in something that resembles a crossover between Batman and Harry Potter, while the bride sports a very Bellatrix Lestrange-ish hairstyle, keeping a semi-Gothic black attire. This is a very special NFT as it showcases what the bride and the groom originally wanted to be in the metaverse wedding reception.

Sheet1.Title: Abuse
Sheet1.Description: I panick each time the door creaks open and reveals your terrifying presence. The trauma it brings, the pain it ignites, the scar it leaves on my already battered soul, the darkness that beclouds the tiny space you left for me, has made me the shadow of myself. Oh! How can i be free from this anguish of your constant abuse? Happiness, laughter, love and care, fled my life the day u took control over me. My worth is like spilt milk on rocks and all my six senses are bruised beyond repair. What is my crime? trust, love, loyalty and patience? I doubt i am still sane. The stigma of your abuse sticks fast.

Sheet1.Title: Windows of Joy
Sheet1.Description: Windows of joy is a piece inspired by the togetherness we explored despite the distance during the pandemic. My school was closed and I was missing my friends but then when my neighbours came to the window and spoke, sang and celebrated the world felt a lot better! The art is a shout out to everyone who was with us during these unprecedented times.

Sheet1.Title: Daemon
Sheet1.Description:
Daemon is a semi-divine spirit, usually created when a noble person or a hero dies. These beings act as a go-between for gods and mortals, delivering divine messages and blessings to mortals or reporting bad behavior to the gods.
 When Cronus, the leader of the Titans, still ruled over the world, he created a “Golden Race” of men. These men were mortal, they lived much like gods, with wonderful strength and pure hearts. When one of the Golden men passed away, he became a Daemon and continued to wander the earth and watch over its future generations.

Sheet1.Title: Woven lives
Sheet1.Description: Don’t look up or around! That is what they want you to do while the planet suffocates little by little for futile profits. ‘Woven lives’ talks about the connection of humans and other species who have an equal right over earth. We are alive only if we cohabit the space and respect this relationship. Yes, climate change is real and No, it is not overrated. All elements here are woven together starting from icebergs to coral reefs, deserts to modern settlements. It is the duty of all to learn everyday practices to contribute less pollution into the bed of the earth. And duty of governments to take effective measures which will put kid activists back to schools because they can finally dream of a future. Do we still have a chance to reverse climate change? Maybe. Yes. Woven lives is just one of the ways in that direction. We have miles to go.

Sheet1.Title: Galaxy Hunters
Sheet1.Description: Galaxy Hunters are anthropomorphic bounty hunters from the planet Kunta, they are a part of an ongoing series of characters for the comic book Rapture Star

Sheet1.Title: Queen Sagittarius
Sheet1.Description:
The queen of constellations, the creator of mystical beings, the goddess of fertility, luck. This artwork depicts the human form of Queen Sagittarius who used to stay among the people during the birth of a child. Sagittarius is a calm and beautiful person and she is the wife of King Taurus where they happened to live as Peasants. 
 
 The art has a monochrome palette for her skin and some colors which highlight her beauty.

Sheet1.Title: Fractal Petal
Sheet1.Description: Fractal Art is endless possibilities of geometry and mathematics represented as visual designs. Fractal patterns are everywhere, principle element of nature. Fractal Petal is a representation of a tiny fraction of that endless possibilities, the pattern, the colors, the design is expression of unseen world of fractal art.

Sheet1.Title: Lucid Dreams
Sheet1.Description:
Our mind is at a constant pace throughout the day, the only time it’s at rest is when we are asleep. Dreams have always been a mysterious part of our lives. These brain-driven hallucinations can feel real no matter how fantastical or surreal and can generate a range of emotions from euphoria to sadness to fear.
 
 Lucid dreams happen when you are able to separate dreams from reality, giving you the ultimate power to have a control over your brain. This artwork is a reminder for you to be the master of your reality as you but no one else is the creator of your own life.

Sheet1.Title: Seraphic
Sheet1.Description:
She is so bright and glorious with flora &fauna surrounded that you cannot look at her face or her garments for the splendor with which she shines. For she is terrible with the terror of the avenging lightning, and gentle with the goodness of the bright sun; and both her terror and her gentleness are incomprehensible to humans…. But she is with everyone and in everyone, and so beautiful is her secret that no person can know the sweetness with which she sustains people, and spares them in inscrutable mercy.”
The three faces in the art represents the willpower unity and freedom each women spreads to the world.

Sheet1.Title: Shackled Inception
Sheet1.Description:
“NOOOO!!!!! You are not supposed to water the plants!”
 “You are on your periods!”
 
 As obscene as it may sound, it's an unfortunate reality in our own homes. Something I happened to hear recently and could not stop myself but discuss with the person. This is not the first and the only thing I’ve came across and pretty sure that I have come nowhere close to the actual harassment that the girls in our society are subjected to.
 
 This piece comes from a very small perspective at how girls/women/non-binary people are viewed. This is not something I can relate to one specific experience but a lot of key observations and perspectives.

Sheet1.Title: Elemental Powers
Sheet1.Description:
Our hands..some people think that hands don't have much power. They are definitely wrong. If there is the right will power and the belief that we can, then we can " Poori jagath ko hila sakthe he " and i always believe in this.
 
 Presenting : Elemental Powers
 
 In the artwork, the flowers and bushes represent the land/earth, then water, fire, the direction and curve of the water drops depicts wind, the smoke represents smoke/clouds & the red circle behind represents the circle of life. The water and fire are shaped as of like hands itself. These all depicts to the fact that hands can control anything.

Sheet1.Title: Yaksha, the Oracle of Fables!
Sheet1.Description: Yakshan, invokes the spirit of the ancestors and becomes a medium of divine intervention. As a dramatis personae, Yakshan assumes different roles, particularly the mythological gods, rendering the possibilities of the folk, classical and rural forms of theatre, and at the same time depicting the moral in the myth.

Sheet1.Title: Fractal Spirals
Sheet1.Description:
Fractal Spirals is algorithmic art created from fractal objects represented by a repetitive mathematical pattern resulting in this form of imagery.
 
 Dimensions: 6000 × 3169

Sheet1.Title: Chaos
Sheet1.Description: Accept that life is uncertain, unpredictable, complicated and fast. Accept it all as it is good, bad, great and every way in-between. Life has always been in chaos so let's get used to it. Accept it and take a step.

Sheet1.Title: Mirage
Sheet1.Description:
Sometimes, beauty- tantalizing, magical, hypnotizing as the undulating motion of fish illuminated in the soft glow of an aquarium- can be a deceptive, cruel thing. 
 
 The fishes, when viewed from beyond the illusory glass, seem as though they are frozen in a patina of perfection, but the turbulence that seethes beneath the stillness is all but invisible to our unseeing eyes. Those beautiful creatures, trapped in a mirage, call to our own souls, trapped in the vice-like grip of the lovely lies we tell ourselves at the behest of the world.

Sheet1.Title: The Companion
Sheet1.Description:
This artwork made using 600 Rubik’s Cubes portrays Lord Krishna, who was the best companion Arjuna had had during his moments of breaking down in the midst of Kurukshetra War. 
 This artwork tries to emphasise the necessity of having, as well as being, that good friend everyone deserves to have.
 
 Details:
 1/1 artwork
 Made with love using 600 Rubik’s Cubes
 Physical size: 6 ft x 4 ft (approx.)
 Weight: 70 kg (150 pounds) approx.

Sheet1.Title: ATHAZAGORAPHOBIA
Sheet1.Description:
The fear of fading into obscurity. With a feeling of madness, it's been curated.
 
 This RARE abstract painting portrays the anxiety of being forgotten in society through pure imagination.
 
 Open for debate and interpretation.

Sheet1.Title: Rediscover Yourself
Sheet1.Description:
An amazing thing happens when you get honest with yourself and start doing what you love, what makes you happy. Your life literally slows down. You stop merely looking forward to special events. You begin to live in each moment. You just ride the wave that is life, with this feeling of contentment and joy. You move fluidly, steadily, calm and grateful. A veil is lifted, and a whole new perspective is born.
 "The world has slowed so you can rediscover yourself.

Sheet1.Title: Gaia: Moeder van het leven
Sheet1.Description:
Gaia: Moeder van het leven is an illustration of the greek goddess of life and earth, Gaia.
 The piece is also a representation of the exquisiteness and strength of women and how they bring life to the world.

Sheet1.Title: Virago
Sheet1.Description:
I am willing to fight for those who can not fight for themselves.The World hurt me I'm not gonna let this happen to anyone else!!
 Her scars and fire in her eyes indicate that she has a painful back story, she has been fighting since she was a child.She grew mentally and emotionally strong through each challenges of life and created herself as a warrior
 an unstoppable, strong and fearless warrior!!

Sheet1.Title: TRANQUIL
Sheet1.Description:
What you think, you become
 What you feel, you attract
 What you imagine, you create."
 - Buddha
 
 'Peace of Mind' is something we seek in the world, but it is something that lies within us. Our mind is one of the most powerful tool, wield it.

Sheet1.Title: Infinite love
Sheet1.Description: Love has no boundries . if you love someone and they also love you nothing can stop you . love makes you do amazing things wich you cant even imagine . and love is the only thing that can change anything . and right now is the much needed thing in the world looking at what's going on in world.

Sheet1.Title: Serene summertime
Sheet1.Description:
This is work from collection "A hundred faces". It's my declaration of love to drawing portraits.
 "Serene Summertime" is about wild wind in our hairs, about first love, about a bittersweet memories, about serene time what we all spent each summer.
 "She wishes this moment would never end, like the wind in her hair.

Sheet1.Title: Strip Away
Sheet1.Description:
I created this piece to visually see all our inner lies, masking personalities and stiffed words all being blown out through the mouth, like a haunting side of our soul is leaving the body. A grey cloud raining and washing away the past and removing the mask.
 
 As a foreign student in Europe, I felt a lot of pressure to hide many aspects of my culture, clothing and thoughts. I was afraid of not being able to fit in. This all stripped away as I grew older and began adding more cultural expressions to my art. It allowed me to flourish with appreciation.

Sheet1.Title: Maya
Sheet1.Description:
Maya
 
 A mystery woman
 Has enormous secrets within
 Someone who dares to be real
 Who knows her capabilities.
 And knows how to turn them into possibilities.
 A queen with an invisible crown who never waited for a king to build her empire.
 Dont go by that soft look on her face,she has fire within. 
 She is me ,she is you ,she is that woman who believes in herself and believes that she can be everything that she decides to be .

Sheet1.Title: Secret Garden
Sheet1.Description:
Does a Tree talk?
 Does a Bird talk?
 Does a river talk?
 
 Yes, it is! There is always Sound amongst the trees in the Garden, but our hearts must be very quiet to hear it.

Sheet1.Title: • Chitrangi Mahal •
Sheet1.Description:
• Chitrangini Mahal • 
 An Indo-Islamic Gem amidst Vijaynagara Architecture
 This artwork is an visual derivative of the Chitrangini Mahal aka Lotus Mahal at Hampi, Karnataka. The lotus-shaped palace is an important secular structure amidst the architecture of Hampi which is mainly of the Vijaynagara style. 
 The monument is literally named after the idea of the architecture it is inspired from "Palace of Lotus". The idea was to revisit a hidden gem of architecture amidst the Vijayanagar landscape that provides a secular perspective to the overall idea of how architecture is perceived.
 The artwork done using #caddforart celebrates the secular aspect of art and how it allows us to look at a complex layer of history that is often overshadowed.

Sheet1.Title: One Way
Sheet1.Description:
Life is a one-way journey
 I can't get my current hours back 
 I can't get my current heartbeats back 
 I can't get my current breath back
 Because life is a one-way journey
 
 I decided to live fully today
 I decided to walk fully today
 I decided to give fully today
 Because life is a one-way journey
 
 I want to spread positivity today
 I want to spread peace today
 I want to spread the love today
 Because life is a one-way journey

Sheet1.Title: Namaste
Sheet1.Description: This piece is dedicated to 'Namaste', our Indian greeting. I grew up with it, as did most of our people. I say it when I first speak with anyone. It felt like in a time of owning our brown-ness, our culture, our heritage, an ode to our greeting depicted by modern Indians of various creeds and lifestyle choices had to be created. That's what this piece represents. Us, the modern India, the NFT India, connected to and confident in our being and all that that means.

Sheet1.Title: BEYOND
Sheet1.Description:
She was a butterfly bringing change, hope and life,
 Finding colours to nirvana trying to get high,
 Powerful yet stable, 
 She brought peace to every eye,
 Watching her move as she fly,
 
 One dark night she saw a light,
 Burning high and low at times,
 Moving free in the sky,
 She saw love in that light,
 Her heart felt warmth and spark in eyes,
 She called her firefly,
 
 One knew love and other knew life,
 Both filled with desires looked in eyes,
 
 Flames in hearts they took each other to worlds apart,
 One ruled the day and other lived the dark,
 With growing feelings they knew the truth too,
 No matter how beautiful it could be,
 They had to be where they were meant to be,
 Wishing for a life where they could grew,
 
 With all the power they had,
 They reached a bridge never seen,
 Connecting both worlds in between,
 Yet somewhere Beyond they could think,
 
 Where stars brought the light and universe gave them life,
 They found love beyond boundaries,
 A connection without lies.

Sheet1.Title: Innocent Company
Sheet1.Description:
Portraying a man with his innocent best friend, gazing at the grandeur of the machine that approaches them. With an orange sunset and the titanic planets as a backdrop. 
 Even with this overwhelming sight, the puppy stays put. Focusing on what’s in front but never forgetting who is beside him.

Sheet1.Title: She's a nomad
Sheet1.Description:
I ve always wanted art to be that widens eyes, with not words but the heart of the person should call it beautiful. 
 I started with the idea of drawing a nomad and somewhat that connects nature. So a women I started to draw with and along the line an amazing traditional clothing with contrast colors. 
 A women cannot not be common, there's always something special, n so I chose a traditional dress with jewels to meet the idea of special. I had a simple thought process- something beautiful and green and that's women and nature. 
 
 I totally drew this on my phone, almost took me a week to complete.

Sheet1.Title: The Shaman
Sheet1.Description: It is beautiful to love as women. Each individually enchanting in their own way, conjuring a legacy of lovemaking in their wake. Generations of memories are passed down to us in the form of stories. Much of what is told no longer relevant as we are different individuals living in different times. Still, there is splendor in how each woman yearned, tried, succeeded or failed yet did not give up on love.Leaving behind the tale of how she bewitched her beloved.

Sheet1.Title: Escaping the Bedlam
Sheet1.Description:
Within the chaotic world, it has become hard for people to live, to even breathe here. All the pessimistic aspects of this world are leading this planet towards a declination in humanity and peace.
 
 Nature is a way out of this chaos. The power of nature is immeasurably immense. One can heal and prosper in the lap of nature. It holds the secret of this world.
 
 This illustration is a representation of how a person is evading the situation of mayhem and is being helped by the lovely nature.
 
 This is also a reminder for all of us, to escape from certain situations which are making us feel suffocated. Be happy, always :)

Sheet1.Title: Self Love
Sheet1.Description:
Embrace the flowers of self love.
 
 The Earth cries out of humanity,
 to respect in rhythmicity.
 To contemplate self you and you will see that;
 
 Even on a beautiful sunny day, 
 not all flowers bloom together.
 To be able to yield to storm
 and yet to grow robust like flowers bloom.
 
 Burn! There are leaf shadows everywhere-
 To live a little longer myself drowning in waves.
 To plant a garden of my soul decorated in flowers.

Sheet1.Title: Divine Waters
Sheet1.Description:
She can drown you, she can cleanse you, she can save you. She is water. 
 Feminine energy is like water, powerful, deep, and pure. Her movement, her power, and her color draw us closer to her. 
 She is the epitome of calm and comfort when she loves, but can turn into raging waves when she is controlled. 
 Let her sacredness be celebrated, let her divinity be admired, and let her purity be a source of healing.
 
 This piece is a celebration of feminine energy, beauty, and power.

Sheet1.Title: The heroes of lockdown
Sheet1.Description: COVID lockdown which was hurriedly imposed on people had left many common people without a source of income and without food & shelter. But we've also seen how 'heroes' emerged from streets to help, feed & support each other including street animals.

Sheet1.Title: Mythos vs Logos
Sheet1.Description:
“Within infinite myths lies the eternal truth
 Who sees it all? 
 Varuna has but a thousand eyes, 
 Indra has a hundred, 
 You and I, only two.” - Devdutt Pattnaik

Sheet1.Title: Bent but not Broken
Sheet1.Description:
I'm bent
 but jot broken,
 I'm scarred
 but not disfigured,
 I'm sad
 but not hopeless,
 I'm afraid
 but now powerless,
 I'm bewildered
 but not giving up

Sheet1.Title: Another Earth
Sheet1.Description:
Another Earth is my fantasy filled imagination of how Earth would be if we ALL decide to live in harmony. The true outcome of WAGMI.
 
 In this village on my Earth, inclusivity is the corner stone of society. 
 
 One case see women doing most traditionally male jobs. Why should boys have all the fun ?
 
 You can see same sex partners existing without persecution.
 
 But does inclusivity stop there ? Nope. In my “Another Earth” you can see human and non-human entities living, working, loving and evolving together.
 
 You can see the a human child adopted by two non human entities.
 
 Now not only do they live in harmony amongst themselves, but also with the Earth. That is why she gives back to them. 
 
 Ploughing at night. Why not. ?
 Rainbows in the moonlight. Why not. ?
 Multi coloured grass and shrub. WHY…NOT ?
 
 Let us find our “new” Earth and when we do let’s not bring in all the pettiness of this earth to our “Another Earth”. 
 
 That may be our final chance..

Sheet1.Title: The Devotional Dance
Sheet1.Description:
This artwork is inspired by Pichwai art and Udaipuri architecture. Pichwai art is known to express one's devotion for Lord Sri Krishna and in this painting, I have tried to express harmony and devotion using balance and symmetry. 
 I have always loved working with patterns and in this painting, you can see an amalgamation of patterns and colours coming together cohesively. 
 May you enjoy this devotional dance.

Sheet1.Title: Tangled thoughts
Sheet1.Description: Fluid art is a form of abstract art that uses acrylic paints with a runny (fluid)consistency. The acrylic paints react with each other when combined together to make interesting and visually organic motifs. This type of art is fun for all ages.

Sheet1.Title: Purple Pages
Sheet1.Description: Purple pages artwork represents the surreal world we escape into when we turn the pages of a book. The colour purple paints a very otherworldly emotion in different shades and this art aims to transport you to that happy place.

Sheet1.Title: Chathurang - The Resilience of Draupadi
Sheet1.Description:
There is a saying " A determined Woman is unstoppable". Chathurang, an ancient game of gamble is related to the greatest war in Indian Mythology when Queen Draupadi's honour and purity was to put to test and her resilience raged a war destroying an evil dynasty.
 This illustration was created with a blend of fractal patterns on handmade sketch and represents how a helpless woman protected her virtues with pure determination in a dreadful circumstance.

Sheet1.Title: Captain of my ship
Sheet1.Description: Inspired from the beautiful quote by Michael Josephson, 'You are the captain of your ship; don't let anyone else take the wheel'. A woman with the stag horns as it is symbol of power, strength, beauty, courage and oar in her hands is self portrait and also a dedication to all the unshakeable women.

Sheet1.Title: Sparkle
Sheet1.Description:
Sparkle is a hand-drawn, 2d mandala art. I loved creating the patterns and especially the dots-and-lines. 
 The name Sparkle comes from the thought that fluttering butterflies appear to me as sparkling; oozing their beauty, colours and magic everywhere they fly. I've loved butterflies ever since I was a child and creating this artwork takes me back to my childhood memories. So, it’s a childhood dream in my style of mandala art.

Sheet1.Title: In Another Life
Sheet1.Description:
In another life, my burdens are replaced by my wings.
 In another life, I'm free because I'm meant to be, 
 Swimming, 
 Far from, and high above the sea. 
 
 Light is the way, soft is my landing, 
 I'm free to move, there's nothing that can stop me. 
 Not weight, not shape, not size, nor colour.
 I'd float like the other,
 Birds of a feather. 
 And yet we'd be different, not ashamed to grow together.
 
 In another life, I'm another creature. 
 Swimming among the clouds,
 And flying with the fish. 
 How I wish,
 I were in yet another life, unburned by this one's strife. 
 Unleashed, uninhibited, undone by the ways that I have been set in.
 A new dawn is on the horizon, and the clouds that I swim between are carrying me forward. 
 Into a newer way, where the sunset is the start of everyday. 
 And when morning comes, we lay to rest. 
 Undoing what those before us
 thought to be best.
 
 -@marilyndcruz

Sheet1.Title: Rebirth
Sheet1.Description: When all seems like an end with so much hurt, loss, pain and sorrow, never forget there is always hope and an innate ability to use the resources within us to rebirth.

Sheet1.Title: I am a Woman Too
Sheet1.Description:
In our society as a consequence of various social differentiation like racism, sexism, classism, etc. a symbolic degradation was created for some specific communities that are lower in stratification. This degradation again contributes to the identity formation of those specific communities. Relating this to the transgender community the stigma and prejudice created by the majority of the society altogether leads to symbolic degradation as well as the formation of identity. In a world where things are most of the time viewed in binary transgender women still search for their identity from a third perspective. They may not be born women, but they are women just like any others. Beautiful, strong, and feminine in every way possible. 
 
 PS: The submitted artwork is AR-enabled. To view the AR version, the artist recommends viewing it using the Artivive app.

Sheet1.Description: Whales live enigmatic lives, in that realm impenetrable to our gaze. Small wonder they’ve seemed magical and strange

Sheet1.Title: C U R I O S I T Y
Sheet1.Description:
The important thing in life is not to stop questioning. Curiosity has its own reason for existence. One cannot help but be in awe when he contemplates the mysteries of eternity, of life, of the marvelous structure of reality and surreal dreams. It is enough if one tries merely to comprehend a little of this mystery each day.
 
 Rightbrainyart | 2022 | 3000x4000px

Sheet1.Title: Arike
Sheet1.Description: Arike is a female name from Yorubaland which mean "Cherished one". Arike is always cared for or pampered on sight. This beautiful name is expressed with a unique style which is "araism

Sheet1.Title: DubDub Maharani
Sheet1.Description: ‘DubDub Maharani’ is dedicated to every girl who is the main character of her story. Everything she wants, she strives for it unapologetically. As opinions & expectations are never-ending, she believes it’s for the best to pay no heed! This piece portrays her fierce, assertive and badass self in the most colourful way.

Sheet1.Title: Dystopia
Sheet1.Description:
What remains of the centuries old city of Kochi is now a dystopian sunset paradise.
 The after effects of pollution caused by the wars of the previous generations have rendered the air harmful for humans. Plants grow inside greenariums, nowhere else and animals are nothing but memorial sculptures by the road.
 Humans have however shielded themselves inside robots to avoid direct exposure to the harmful atmospheric light & air. As time passed by, the robots became more than just mechanical units, rather people began to consider them as expressions of genderless fashion. Slowly due to lack of other interesting avenues of expression, the society began to deeply focus on excessive display of fashion on robots to the extent where it became a normal to do so. Thus a high fashion society was born in 2200 AD.
Sparkles is an Audio Visual NFT, which tries to capture surrealism in a digital media, to mesmerize the viewer.

Sheet1.Title: Wasted Life
Sheet1.Description:
A normal person spends an average of 3 hours a day on social media
 That's a huge part of our life wasted which could've been used for something else
 That could be learning a new skill, traveling, or even spending time with our family
 Social media is great, But it needs a limit,
 By living a life scrolling through our phones all the time we are wasting our own creativity and potential
 Instead of overconsuming, we should try to spend that time on something that we like, 
 Every time when we use social media we are traveling through a loop that makes us want to use it again
 The piece Wasted life tells us how overconsumption can affect anyone. The astronaut in the piece can represent every single one of us if we are overconsuming social media
 So next time when you're overconsuming just remember that you're wasting a part of your life that could've been an even better memory.

Sheet1.Title: Analog Future
Sheet1.Description: Since there exists a strong culture for analog supercars in the automotive community, this artwork is a digital reincarnation of a 90s supercar that essentially describes the endless possibilities in the metaverse.

Sheet1.Title: Floating Away
Sheet1.Description:
This is a silhouette 3D animation of a Boat sailing in the ocean and watching it inside a cave with an aesthetic evening vibe to it.
 
 I was thinking about what to create for my submission for #namasteyNFTBLR and on the 23rd night at 1 am I got a call from my friends were at the front gate of my home and we just took the car and went in search of the nearest Beach and that was the only plan that we had in our mind. We reached the nearest beach which was like 120 km away and we reached there a bit early I mean 4 in the morning and there was no light we waited it out, The waiting was worth it and the beach we went to was a bit different the shore was a bit long and the sun came up the ocean came out. And there was a boat that was there and that got me an idea of making this piece. 
 
 Created on Blender.

Sheet1.Title: Coherence
Sheet1.Description:
Vicious fins lurk in abundance,
 The will of the prey rises at once.
 Our colors merge and differences fade
 An instinctual order in the depths of chaos.
 Knit tight and built strong
 through currents warm and cold all along.
 Closely guarding one and all, 
 the might of a coherent whole.
 
 
 43 seconds
 1920 x 1080
 original soundtrack

Sheet1.Title: Eluder
Sheet1.Description: There's something about shadows because you assume what's lurking in them.

Sheet1.Title: The Praying Lotus
Sheet1.Description:
The praying lotus is made entire out of code and visual scripting. It follows the golden ratio spiral mathematical equation, and was made to understand the unification of the verses. 
 An attempt to understand the algorithm of the infinite, through meditation.

Sheet1.Title: Time
Sheet1.Description:
The cogs in the watch carry on. 
 
 As life unravels about us, we spin in an infinite cycle of regrets; of the could have beens and have beens.
 
 But we hold together and soldier on. For the scars are nothing but sprinkles. Like confetti blasted on a watch, and the cogs always go on, as we soldier on.

Sheet1.Title: Old Chibi Totoro
Sheet1.Description:
This artwork is representation of tranquility and the serene life of the old Totoro the Bunny, enjoying the beauty of nature in its own way. The scene captures the life it has had and things it has been through, emphasizing on the fact that journey is more important than the destination. 
 Anime has always been a major part of my life ever since I was a kid. When I learned the skills to make 3D art, I wanted to use it to pay tribute to the things I love in my own way. So this is the aesthetic, hyper realistic version of my art piece of the legendary myth, old chibi totoro.

Sheet1.Title: Citadel
Sheet1.Description:
Citadel:
 A castle on high ground inside or outside a city where people seeks refugees while there's been an emergency or war attack on that city
 
 The Kenneth Castle serves as a bunker during ancient times in Jasper City. Millions are dying, getting scattered during war times, several seeks refugees, shelter and are residing inside this castle. It is a giant fortress surrounded by deadly traps, wild animals and its confusing geometrical structure making it unable to surpass its perimeter.
 Today we can see its remains covered in ivys, mosses which can be a perfect tourist and adventurous spot for the people who want to experience this massive fortress' atmosphere.

Sheet1.Title: The Lost Face
Sheet1.Description:
An enormous Face emerging from the very own city's heart can be a sensation and heart wrenching topic among the civilians but its a matter of fact that it could be a reason for an upcoming mass destruction and havoc in the city.
 ~ The Daily News

Sheet1.Title: Diamanté
Sheet1.Description: Diamanté" is one of my favorite pieces I did , I don't wanna describe it much in words cuz imo art should describe itself to the viewer :)

Sheet1.Title: Toxic love.

Sheet1.Title: Confluence of Colors at Braj.
Sheet1.Description:
Braj ki Holi famously played in Mathura and Vrindavan, in Uttar Pradesh. 
 I travel there every year to witness the festivities. The celebration begins a week early 
 and looks quite different in the towns of Barsana and Nandgaon than the rest of the 
 country. Walking in the footsteps of Lord Krishna, the men of Nandgaon (Krishna’s 
 village) head to Barsana (Radha’s village) to play Holi; the next day, the men of Barsana 
 travel to Nandgaon with colours. In both the villages, the local women “beat” the 
 visiting young men with sticks, just like Radha and the gopis did to little Krishna. But 
 Lathmaar Holi (Holi of sticks) is more of a festive dance than a confrontation. On the 
 third day, residents of both the villages get together and head over to Vrindavan to play 
 Phoolon ki Holi (Holi of flowers). 
 — ROHIT GADHER ON HIS PHOTOGRAPH, TAKEN WITH A SAMSUNG GALAXY A72 IN MARCH 2021

One day a bit intoxicated, he set fire to shrubs in order to clean up the place. Unexpectedly, the fire spread off and kelan was in the midst, fire all around him. There was no way to escape and kelan climbed a tree as a last resort. Alas, there were 2 snakes on the tree. Kelan and snakes fell into the burning fire.Kelan met with death along the snake. It was the time when Wayanatt kulavan (God) had set out for his daily hunting and he happened to pass through this area. Vayanatt kulavan on seeing the burnt body of Kandanar Kelan, touched his body with his bow. Kelan got his life back immediately. Kandanar Kelan who got a rebirth.

Sheet1.Title: DAIVAS - The Demi-Gods
Sheet1.Description:
Bootha Kola or Kola Aata also known as the worship of Daivas or Bhootas or Demi-Gods, is an ancient ritual prevalent among the Tulu speaking community in the Dakshina Kannada districts in Karnataka and in kasargod taluk of kerala,which is collectively referred to as Tulu Nadu.
 Bhootha kola is based on a simple belief that several bhoothas or daivas (guardian spirits) protect the villages in Tulunadu. Historically, Tuluvas did not believe in God, they only believed in bhootas. Tulavas believe that these bhootas once walked the land as humans, and everyone joins them after death.
 
 These bhootas are invoked and personified by a paatri (an individual from the Nalike community who impersonates the bhoota at bhootaradhane) during the annual festival of bhootaradhane. 
 
 Hope you got to know about another ancient ritual art form from southern part India via this image.

Sheet1.Title: Twins
Sheet1.Description: I met the twins named Ali and Hasan on a photo trip. I found out that their mother passed away at the birth of Ali and Hasan. It has come to my attention that twins are not separated from each other in the real world as they are in the womb. It was obvious from this fact that they would all be together in their later lives

Sheet1.Title: Asura
Sheet1.Description:
The Ashura Mourning Ceremony was held in Istanbul on the anniversary of Hz.Hüseyin's martyrdom in Karbala. One of the moments I caught.
 The little girl watched the thousands of people grieving around her. Her gaze was a little confused, but very innocent. I felt the drama of a massacre that took place centuries ago. That moment.
 
 During mourning, knives and cutting tools are not touched, sacrificed, and meat is not eaten. No living thing is tortured during mourning. The basic principle of the Mourning Fast is not to break anyone's heart, not to hurt anyone with one's tongue, not to gossip about anyone. Those in good health fast. The purpose of mourning is not to torture oneself, but to commemorate and not forget so that evil and massacres do not happen again

Sheet1.Title: Harran houses
Sheet1.Description: I took this photo in acient city of Şanlıurfa/Harran.Domed structures, which you see in this photo,are used as a house by people for 200 years. It is impossible to see similar of this photo. Because, the area, where I took the photo, has a desert climate. And snowfall is very rare there. I feel lucky because I got the chance of taking photo of this area in snowy and foggy weather. My this photo won national and international awards. At last, It won the first prize in Turkey Press Photo of the Year

Sheet1.Title: olive oil making
Sheet1.Description:
On my trip in 2018, I went to the Hatay region. I really liked the cultural life of Hatay. People of many faiths live together. The main source of income is olive and olive oil production.
 
 Olive oil is made with the traditional method. Olives collected from the trees are cleaned and poured into the pool. crushes olives with the help of a large stone horse. The oil from the crushed olives is collected. Olive farming is a source of livelihood in Hatay region.
 
 This photo of me won the 1st prize in the İzmir Commodity Exchange Competition.

Sheet1.Title: worker
Sheet1.Description: Charcoal is formed through a long and tiring process. People work in dense smoke. Because of this, people experience health problems. This process begins with the burning of oak trees. The fire is covered and burned for a while. turns off after a while. In this way, coal is formed.

Sheet1.Title: geometry and human
Sheet1.Description: I took this photo in Erzurum Turkey in 2018. The photographs in the frame on the back wall of this building belong to Foto Reporter Ara Güler, who sheds light on Turkish photography. I really liked the geometry of the building. The light falling on the stairs was enchanting, I had asked someone to pass by, and soon luck was on my side. Ara Güler died by chance the year I took this photo.

Sheet1.Title: pepperman
Sheet1.Description: Cumali, the son of a family working as farm workers, had created his own playground among the peppers. He wanted to pose for me when he saw that I was taking a picture. We played with him first. While playing the game, we talked about his dreams about the future. After chatting with his family and drinking tea, I broke up with them. Cumali's smile was reflected in my photo.

Sheet1.Title: Fishermen
Sheet1.Description:
When it's time to go fishing in Istanbul during the winter months, fishermen throw their nets into the sea. Meanwhile, the seagulls fly around the fishing boats.
 I see and watch the fishing boats as a scene. During the winter months, magnificent views appear on the Bosphorus.
 I take pictures of moments that I find interesting and special.
 I love watching the sea, the smell of iodine and the fishermen.

Sheet1.Title: dust and labor
Sheet1.Description: Labor is the most valuable thing in the world. Working in very difficult conditions is a lot of effort. I took this photo for my charcoal workers project that I went to for 3 years. Charcoal is produced in a place close to Istanbul and there are many workers working here.These workers breathe this dust fume every day and they work in these conditions.Sometimes the eye can't see because of the dust and smoke.

Sheet1.Title: Pleasure of bathing
Sheet1.Description:
This photo I took in December 2018 is called the pleasure of bathing. Enjoying a hot spring in the Güroymak district of Bitlis while the freezing cold negatively affects life. The buffalo and horses left in the barns in winter are washed in the hot spring. The scenery that emerges while the young people of the village both bathe and have fun in the hot spring, where the hot and healing water emerges from meters deep, is indispensable for photography enthusiasts from all over Turkey.
 I attended their party when I took this photo.

Sheet1.Title: wild horses running away from their fears
Sheet1.Description: wild horses don't run very fast unless they have someone chasing them. What makes horses run so fast is that they run away from their pursuers. They stay away from people because they are wild. If they see a person approaching them, they either run away from it or attack. When I took this photo, I prayed that the horses wouldn't attack me. I had a chance because they didn't attack me. It was a pretty dusty day. When I came back and washed my hair, mud was running from my head. The stories of difficult photos are beautiful and the most beautiful thing is "hard photos are always beautiful.

Sheet1.Title: traveling salesman
Sheet1.Description: Traveling vendors visit remote villages once a month. They bring sweets that the kids love so much. In villages, instead of money, eggs, wheat, etc. products are exchanged. Hearing the horn of the car, the village children gather in the square. All children share this joy. Parents also meet their children's stationery needs in exchange for pulses. Traveling vendors are a culture that disappeared with the opening of markets in villages.

Sheet1.Title: The Scream Of Nature
Sheet1.Description:
We are destroying nature. Do you feel responsible?
 Do you hear the cry of nature? While some are upset, some are looking out for their own interests.
 When the last tree dries up, we will know how much damage we have done when the last lake is destroyed.

Sheet1.Title: Vishwamitra and Menaka
Sheet1.Description:
A paradigmatic representation of Vishwamitra and Menaka by one of the oldest practicing Behrupia (Impersonator)
 
 The Story- The sage and seductress is a common trope in Hindu mythology.
 Indra, the king of gods, gets worried about the intensity of Vishwamitra’s ascetic practice as it would give the sage enormous powers. He sends Menaka to seduce him and nullify his penance.

Sheet1.Title: A bunch of happiness
Sheet1.Description: Our model opened her eyes to the world with cesarean section.  The pediatrician did all his checks and they posed for me together.

Sheet1.Title: Friend
Sheet1.Description: There were curfews during the Covid-19 pandemic, which surrounded the whole world. It was the children who were most affected by this. School education continued in their home online. Bored at home, this boy sought a friend. He made friends with the ornamental fish in the house. He is feeding his friend while he is eating an apple. I hope these troubled days will not happen again.

Sheet1.Title: Family
Sheet1.Description: Even in our saddest moments, don't cats draw all the attention to themselves and make us forget everything? Aunt Hazan is a woman living alone, she lost her husband, she has no children, she lost her mother, she adopted these four puppies and they are not alone anymore, they are very happy together.

Sheet1.Title: Bulgur
Sheet1.Description:
Bulgur is an indispensable part of Turkish cuisine. Wheat is boiled in large boilers, poured into large areas in the facilities with trailers, left to dry under the sun for 2 days and mixed with the help of rakes attached to the tractors to lose the moisture it contains. Dried wheat is collected by tractors and turned into bulgur after cracking. 
 This photo was taken at a bulgur factory in Gaziantep, which is a city located on Mesopotamia, home land of the wheat.
 
 Photographer: Serhat Karasungur
 Location: Gaziantep/ Turkey
 Date: 23.09.2017
 Dimensions: 3600* 2400 - 300dpi

Sheet1.Title: Spiritual Awakening
Sheet1.Description:
Varanasi is the most holy city in Hinduism and the spiritual home of India's Sadhus, or holy men who have renounced the worldly life. They are revered by Hindus as representatives of the Gods and sometimes worshiped as Gods themselves. 
 
 Their personalities, practices differ from each other and there's a concern that this heritage would be lost in the fast urbanisation of Varanasi. With industrialisation and tourism attracting thousands, I felt the need to preserve this heritage through photographs.
 
 The Sadhu in the frame is Praying at 5AM in Manikarnika Ghat - The oldest Burning Ghat of Varanasi. The Smoke in the background is coming out of Burning Bodies as it was the peak of COVID in India and there was a Queue of Dead Bodies waiting to be cremated at the ghat. 
 
 Photographer : Ayush Dixit
 
 Edition : 1/1
 
 Location : Varanasi , India .
 
 Year Created : 2021
 
 Gear : Smartphone - Vivo V20PRO
 
 Genre : Street Photography .

Sheet1.Title: The Queen's Guards
Sheet1.Description:
The Victoria Memorial is a huge white marble structure in Central Kolkata, which was built between 1906 and 1921. It is dedicated to the memory of Queen Victoria, now a museum under the auspices of the Ministry of Culture, and is the largest monument in the world which is dedicated to a royal. 
 
 This shot was taken on the day of Vijay Diwas in 2019. I framed Victoria with the trees and the helicopters (as part of the Vijay Diwas celebration) added life to the frame!
 
 
 India celebrates Vijay Diwas on December 16 to commemorate its victory over Pakistan in the 1971 war, which led to the creation of Bangladesh. On this day, Indians pay homage to the brave soldiers of our country.

Sheet1.Title: The Burning Train
Sheet1.Description:
I clicked this shot while coming from Bhopal in Telangana Express. I was traveling on the same train and that's my bogie which starts burning at 8 am. It is one of the toughest documentation I have done because the temperature was 40+ degrees Celsius and I was carrying my luggage and camera bag while shooting.
 We all were stuck in the middle of nowhere and there is no water. But because this is a very important moment or documentation I decided to cover it in full. Because of the smoke, it was very difficult for me to take a breath.
 In the future, I'll update my full documentation on NFT :)

Sheet1.Title: Alone in the rain
Sheet1.Description: There is nothing like walking with the smell of the sea after the rain. Walking and thinking about life...

Sheet1.Title: Berivan
Sheet1.Description:
Berivan"
 It means a woman who takes care of animals and milks them. At the same time, the name of a rare mountain flower is Berivan.
 I took this photo in Turkey Hakkari-Çukurca.
 He received a Special Award in the photography marathon organized by Çukurça District Governor's Office.

Sheet1.Title: Metallic Consoles
Sheet1.Description:
Two minutes long exposure shot (using 16-stop ND filter) of Central Park Towers, a multi-building complex in Dubai International Financial Centre, Dubai.
 
 Taking such long exposure shot on a cloudy day in Dubai is itself a challenge as you hardly see any clouds throughout the year in this part of the world.
 
 Then comes the editing part which is very time-consuming for such an outcome. The process of editing these long exposure shots is totally unique. Using the pen tool, hard selections are made of different elements in the image. Sometimes these selections take days if you have to make too many selections. Later using these selections while playing with the darks (shadows) and lights (highlights) the final envisioned version of the image is brought forward. Finally, you feel happy and more confident with all the time and efforts you spent to create the masterpiece.

Sheet1.Title: Winged World
Sheet1.Description:
Winged world' explores the eco-scapes of the birds, dwindling under the incessant assault of mankind’s push to adapt the world to itself. 
 
 This frame captures a singular bird species encircled within its own diminishing biosphere. As the sphere shrinks so do the no of birds!! The sky, land, and water in the frame highlight the interconnected nature of this ‘ornithosphere’ and calls to mind the significance of all flora, fauna, and the earth as a whole, which has been pushed to the sidelines in the vision for human progress!!!

Sheet1.Title: Breakfast time
Sheet1.Description: I clicked this picture in 2020 while I was shooting birds at lake at sunrise time. I saw these birds chasing for there breakfast and fishing from lake, then this idea came in my mind to click one picture with sun that looks like the bird is taking sun with it for it’s breakfast. That’s how “Breakfast time” is created.

Sheet1.Title: The Girl who wore the jungle around her.
Sheet1.Description: I still remember standing in front of the waiting line, looking at different models go in and out wearing nothing but dreams that were made from nights of tears and sweat. Every piece felt like it was worth clicking but then came the girl who wore the jungle around. I describe it as a jungle because it captures all the bizarre earthly beauty you might find during a jungle trek. The vibrant and bright colours complement the sober plain background. The ramp light beaming through the backdrop mimics the brightness of the sunbeams making it's way through the canopy of the jungle. The model carries the piece with utter raw confidence, almost as if she were born in it.

Sheet1.Title: The golden hour at Leh
Sheet1.Description: As a photographer, it’s important to have a perspective for the right picture. This is a capture from the Tsemo hill, while one can see an Ariel view of the old town of Leh. The magic happened when the sun set down and the view suddenly turned into a beautiful painting. An unimaginable dust of gold on the entire city and the Himalayan mountains at the boundaries, how could I not capture it? It’s one of the most memorable experience I have had on my journey of life.

Sheet1.Title: Golden catch in a golden light…
Sheet1.Description: Was clicked at the beautiful golden light and the timing was perfect when the fishermen were fishing at lake Inle, Myanmar

Sheet1.Title: Heaven is right here
Sheet1.Description:
Our crew went ahead in a rush to reach the summit for the sunset view, Me and my friend were trailing behind them enjoying the journey. All of a sudden the sky started taking its shape and dynamics, clouds paved the way for rays to reach the valley and village below, small streams reflected them like diamonds, the tea plantation's color danced to the flow of clouds, nature at its utmost beauty and we shouted "heaven is right here".
 Artist : James Fotografia

Sheet1.Title: Polar Express
Sheet1.Description:
I got off the train straight in the snow, and started to walk. An Asian filming crew was here, filming at the train passing on the bridge. I was not the only one here for it. A little bit further, at the end of the track, a van was waiting for them, and I felt like we will be a lot on the spot that day. I walked 45 minutes, from the top of the bridge to the photo spot. During the walk the van of the filming crew passed me. This time no doubt, I will see them down the road.
 
 I arrived and they were all here, cameras settled up, waiting for the next train. After a short talk with them I learned that they were filming for a Japanese TV travel documentary that runs the world by train since 1987, called « Sekai no shako kara » which means Views of the World by a train. That kind of funny random meetings you make along the roads. Hope they did get what they wanted from that day shooting the Polar Express.
 
 Artist: Joffrey Briaud
 Size: 4119x6182
 License: Unlimited Commercial

Sheet1.Title: Crying River
Sheet1.Description: A simple summer day, a storm that just passed, a green valley in the French Alps and a river full of water flowing in its middle. The birds sang and I stood there, looking around. The passage of time marked by the flow of the river, observing the sun slowly descending behind the mountains. What a wonderful day

Sheet1.Title: The stone King
Sheet1.Description: My journey in searching the most astonishing mountain has bring me here, in this majestic scenario, embedded in a hidden area, to admire this King. The locals call it the "Stone king" cause the legend tell that there was a king, loved by all the people whom made a period of great well-being, but after his last battle to defend his lands, he was fell, and he was buried underneath this mountain, cause the king must rest under another king.

Sheet1.Title: Heading out to the Highway
Sheet1.Description: On August 2, 2018, I traveled nearly 300 miles chasing storm after storm, but with no luck.  Finally,  I made one final attempt by driving east of this mountain range along the Arizona/New Mexico border and had to rely on instinct to anticipate where this storm would form.  I was well beyond any cell coverage that would provide me with data pointing to where the lightning would be dropping.  To my wonder, the storm lit up right near the end of this lonely highway, and I danced like no one was watching, because no one WAS watching!

Sheet1.Title: Walk through wonderland
Sheet1.Description: Of bridges, between seasons | A boy strolls through the freshly fallen snow in Sopore, Kashmir .

Sheet1.Title: Candyland
Sheet1.Description:
Life can become sweeter when you change your perspective. 
 
 I have spent a lot of time on Google Earth. Trying to find inspiration and locations of places other photographers don’t tell you about. Several years ago, I heard of this rainbow land, and when asked everyone told me to go find it myself.
 
 The hunt for finding where to go, following the bread crumbs and figuring out if it’s possible, and then actually going and seeing if it’s what you think it was from a satellite image... is intoxicating. It makes the images a reward for the work that when into researching and finding it. 
 
 This drone image of one of the most unique landscapes I have ever seen was my reward for several years of researching, waiting for a chance to get here, and planning.

Sheet1.Title: Dreamy day after snowfall
Sheet1.Description:
I went to Kashmir for the first time in 2nd week of January 2021. The plan was to stay there for a week, but extended the tour in the hopes of snowfall and was blessed with snowfall in Srinagar in the last week. Snowfall turned the whole city into white beauty.
 
 On the next day I was blessed with this beautiful cloud porn in Dal lake. To witness snowfall on the previous day and this cloud porn on the next day was just like cherry on the cake.
 
 This beautiful landscape covered in snow with amazing clouds and it's clear reflection in Dal Lake just felt like a beautiful dream. I got to know why Kashmir is called "Heaven on Earth" when I witnessed this peaceful view in Srinagar.

Sheet1.Title: Journey of Souls
Sheet1.Description:
Having visited and marveled several tropical beaches during my photography sojourns, I wasn’t prepared for the sheer breath-taking beauty of the black sand beach at Reynisfjara, Iceland. the frothy crashing waves, piercing cold wind, jaw-dropping basalt columns, colour-rich lava formations and the expansive black ash pebble beach was God’s tapestry come alive before my eyes.
 This click might just have been missed ! Towards the end of a full day on the beach, walking and jesting with friends, capturing the beauty of the place, it was pack up time to further continue the journey. Just as I was walking away, I looked back one last time, camera still in hand, this frame was waiting to be captured – ash grey skies contrasted with silver waves against the hillocks, which comes to my mind as - ‘Journey of Souls’.

Sheet1.Title: Songs of Nature
Sheet1.Description:
Earth is the art and photographer is just a witness. Sometimes nature really surprises you as a photographer. I had been shooting for the whole of morning and when I thought I was done shooting, I packed my tripod and started taking a stroll by the bank of this beautiful lake. And that is when I spotted this wonderful composition with trees and golden hues of sunrise. The mist around the castle makes the image ethereal.

Sheet1.Title: Floating on Reflection
Sheet1.Description: The image shows green waters of a Dam reservoir near Jammu, India. The water turns green only for a few winter months, when the water is very clean. Is the water green due to reflecting the trees above it, or due to the trees submerged within? That's a mystery for me too!

Sheet1.Title: Tranquil
Sheet1.Description: Taken in early morning at Mydala Kere Lake, Karnataka. Just after moving back to Bangalore after being away for 2 years, I could not wait to explore some new places near the city. This location was the best place I could have gone, it was a blissful moment seeing the sunrise in fogy morning.

Sheet1.Title: The Magical Land
Sheet1.Description: Created this photography with the help of my drone light painting resemble photography is not less then magic.

Sheet1.Title: Balance
Sheet1.Description:
Balance came to me after a three hour hike in the dark to catch the sunrise over Colchuck lake, near Leavenworth WA on a crisp fall morning. Subalpine Larches were in full show mode with their bright golden tones. The water was perfectly still. Beautiful suns rays slowly lit the lake up as I sat and ate some breakfast, while reflecting on life. 
 Balance mirrors the Yin and Yang in our lives.

Sheet1.Title: SURVIVAL OF THE FITTEST
Sheet1.Description:
Antlions are known for their fierce predatory habits in larvae stage. While much is not known about the adults (due to short life span) and are nocturnal predators. In the day they are quite docile. 
 Green Lynx Spiders are the apex predators of the day.
 This photo was taken in the monsoon month of 2021 where we see the predator of the day hunts on the predator of the night in a natural history moment. The photo was taken in a thickly wooded area near my house (an old nursery) which was abandoned due to Covid restrictions and has became a safe haven and breeding ground for many insects during the season. Green lynx spider takes enough time to feed on its prey (sometime hours) giving enough opportunity to take photos with proper settings. 
 To takes this photo external light source (Flash with homemade diffuser) was used as light becomes a crisis in the bushes in wooded areas during cloudy monsoon days. 
 This photograph is in the finals of HIPA 2021-22-Nature (winner yet to be declared)

Sheet1.Title: Ms. Angel Eyes
Sheet1.Description:
When I first saw this fluffy puppy, I was blown away by its beauty. This cute Alien is Hyllus diardi, which belongs to a family of jumping spiders that don’t build webs to trap their prey but are ambush hunters with phenomenal hunting skills.
 Hyllus diardi are one of the most famous jumpers in the world and are found only in the mangrove forests of Singapore, India, China, Thailand, Indonesia, Laos and Myanmar. Macro photogs travel to Singapore to shoot this jumper as it is a rarity among jumping spider lovers. I feel lucky to have this beautiful jumper. Jumpers have 8 eyes and it will be enlightening to learn how it uses all its eyes to track its prey.
 Superpower: Hyllus diardi can leap up to 20 times their body length. Humans in comparison can jump only upto 5 times their body length.

Sheet1.Title: Nexus
Sheet1.Description:
For this photography the interaction between the physics of foam construction and its visual impact is what drove me. The image perfectly exploit the connection among science and the inherent artistic appeal of soap bubbles.
 Foams are ubiquitous in daily life, they are made by the union of small bubbles and despite the visual balance conveyed by these arrangements, their structure has a complex and delicate construction. When you look at a bubble, what you're really seeing is some air trapped inside a thin film, consisting of two outer layers of soap that surround an inner layer of water.
 Through this photo the observer is taken to an extreme approximation of the foam’s morphology. From this standpoint it's possible to admire these elegant skeletal structures with an almost surreal appearance, making them appear unfamiliar, and sometimes even strange, capturing the impressive aesthetic perfection of these bubbles.

Sheet1.Title: Princess with her pollen tiara
Sheet1.Description: A beautiful jumping spider hid insider a flower and reappeared, with a pollen tiara on her head.

Sheet1.Title: carousel
Sheet1.Description: No matter how old I get, going to amusement park will remain the most ertertaining thing in the world.

Sheet1.Title: Golden Ratio Stair
Sheet1.Description: The shape of this ladder was very similar to the golden ratio. This is the interior staircase of an ancient ruined mansion. Some people call this mansion the haunted mansion. It is now under protection for renewal. I took a photo of a woman with her local clothes on the golden-ratio staircase of the mansion. The woman was placed at the golden ratio point according to the direction of the light. Thus, I think it is a very effective photograph as a composition.

Sheet1.Title: Bhor Bhaye
Sheet1.Description: A conceptual portrait depicting the aesthetics and beauty of Indian Tribal Woman.

Sheet1.Title: When the eyes tell the story.
Sheet1.Description:
The picture was taken from the village of Taskam in Ladakh. The hidden beauty of Thasakam village, especially the people there, the whole village area. One day, I went to a local madrassa and there were a lot of children in the village and only one's different eyes from all the children attracted me. It was bright with sunlight and a coffee color.
 
 His eyes were drawn to me among the children, and the sunlight coming through the window brightened his eyes.
 
 Suddenly, he looked at me and as soon as I took the photo, it was a beautiful moment, because his eyes were sharp and shining with sunlight, which brought this photo to life.

Sheet1.Title: Mother, seasonal worker
Sheet1.Description:
The burden of being forced to work as a seasonal worker in the far fields of Anatolia is very heavy. In order to make a living, an entire family has to work in the fields during the harvest season. They have to live in makeshift tents for months as a labour community.
 While I was working on my documentary project about them I visited a tent village where they live temporarily in 2009.
 She was sitting with her daughter in the tent where they were forced to live during harvest season. 
 I asked for permission to go inside the tent and take some pictures of them. 
 We chatted a bit but both were shy.
 I felt the burden of the difficult living conditions on her shoulders she had to endure while she was looking at me. 
 It was so emotional moment for me as a photographer.
 Rural of Konya city, Turkey, 2009.

Sheet1.Description: Look close enough and you'll see inside the soul.

Sheet1.Title: Himalayan mother and child
Sheet1.Description: What you see in a portrait is not just some subject, but a living person just like you and me. they have loved ones, they are special and unique to many. Sheet1.Title: Escaping the Bedlam
Sheet1.Description:
Within the chaotic world, it has become hard for people to live, to even breathe here. All the pessimistic aspects of this world are leading this planet towards a declination in humanity and peace.
 
 Nature is a way out of this chaos. The power of nature is immeasurably immense. One can heal and prosper in the lap of nature. It holds the secret of this world.
 
 This illustration is a representation of how a person is evading the situation of mayhem and is being helped by the lovely nature.
 
 This is also a reminder for all of us, to escape from certain situations which are making us feel suffocated. Be happy, always :)

Sheet1.Title: Care
Sheet1.Description: Capturing this picture and watching it again and again makes me thing of so many things reflected though it. Caring for each other and building bridges between generations, being guided and cared from the elderly and caring for the youngsters. This is what makes us humans and this is how we built a strong respectful community.

Sheet1.Title: happy friendship
Sheet1.Description: Ali is a shepherd boy when he is not going to school, and he loves horses. He spends time with his horses whenever he finds time. When I visited the village, I caught this wonderful view while spending time with his horses again.

Sheet1.Title: Happiness
Sheet1.Description: No matter how old a person is, one should not lose hope. Because hope keeps people alive and connects them to life more tightly. The old man, who lived alone in the same house for years after losing his wife, and with whom even the spider in the glassless window became a friend, looks at life in a happy and hopeful way despite all these negativities. The joy of the old man, who is looking forward to the arrival of his grandchildren to visit him on the feast day, can be seen in his eyes.

Sheet1.Title: Untamed
Sheet1.Description:
Be strong, be confident, be intelligent, be witty, be klutzy, be interesting,be funny, be adventurous, be crazy, be talented.
 Be your own definition of amazing, be you.
 That is so much more important than being just beautiful.

Sheet1.Title: Prima Donna
Sheet1.Description: This image was taken in Iowa Park, Texas, a small town just outside of Wichita Falls. Ashlyn Keith, the model, was a ballet dancer, so the shoot was based on a beautiful ballerina, trapped in an attic. It was taken in the attic of an old, run down barn.

Sheet1.Title: Lady In Red
Sheet1.Description: I don’t see passion in red. Nor do I feel irrepressible love. I feel this transcendental calm - of a rose tinted world

Sheet1.Title: Carefree days and sweet memories of childhood.
Sheet1.Description: When I framed this shot, it instantly transported me back to childhood. It reminisces about a time when there was no tension in our lives, where going out to play seemed joyful and satisfying. The innocent laughs and blissful days are momemts which we miss the most and looking back now they bring a wide smile on my face every single time.

Sheet1.Title: Aghori
Sheet1.Description: The Aghori are a small group of ascetic Shaiva sadhus. The Aghori believe themselves to be the masters of many spiritual powers; able to cure mental and physical illnesses, saving lives. The man approaches a pile of ashes on the ground and spreads them over his body and face. “Holy ash is the last and purest state of everything.

Sheet1.Title: Stenzin
Sheet1.Description:
Stenzin is the cutest kid I met during my visit to a village school in Ladakh .
 He was so excited to see me with my camera , he immediately posed for me ! 
 Later after his school he took me around his village for sightseeing .

Sheet1.Title: One lucky meerkat
Sheet1.Description: The Princess had captured a  Meerkat from the wild and made him her pet.

Sheet1.Title: Sign-Age
Sheet1.Description: Time is hardly measurable but age is always measured. Age always leaves its signature on human beings that is mostly visible as wrinkles on the face. It's frightening to notice someone's age on the face. But these wrinkles are the prized possession of someone who feels mature enough. I had an opportunity to meet a woman at Rishikesh on World Photography Day (19th August 2014), who impressed me with intriguing wrinkles on her face that spoke volumes of how time has played with her life.

Sheet1.Title: immigration and life
Sheet1.Description:
This photo is part of a work carried out for two years in the forest of Güzelbahçe in Izmir, in western Turkey. The images document the daily life of children belonging to a minority, the Kurdish, coming from the eastern part of the country. These families where pushed into exile at the 90’s. They had to leave their homes, their lands, their beloved ones.
 
 Nowadays, they survive working on the production of wood charcoal. Each member of the family, from the elder to the youngest, men of woman, participate in every task of this work. Every day, every time, their daily life is done of carring on, cutting, burning, separating, carring on and breathing once and again. Once and again their daily life is done of fire, smoke, dust and black.

Sheet1.Title: Fading Souls
Sheet1.Description:
Fading Souls have always been incredibly special to me, mostly because of the fact that how the fog creates an atmosphere of suspense. The concealing attributes, the mystery of what lies further down the road, what the cyclist and the people coming out of the fog have witnessed through their journey, is very intriguing to me.
 
 This photographs was taken at around 6, in a chilly December morning, on the streets of Kolkata, India. Photographed using a Nikon D3500 and a 50mm 1.8, the layers of people behind the subject slowly fading into the background with reducing visibility, is another reason why this photograph really speaks to me.

Sheet1.Title: Rain in the "Creator's" Den!
Sheet1.Description:
Right out of the 300-year-old idol making hub of Calcutta, India, Kumartuli, this photograph portrays a striking moment that I captured last year with heavy droplets of rain rolling down the wooden fringes and an artist rushing back to his workshop; the shadow of a freshly created idol peeping out is the testimony of their craft, sheathed with persistence.
 
 As the largest festival in Bengal “Durga Puja” sets in, the workload of the skilled artisans increases exponentially and they pray to the Divine Goddess hoping the rain stays away. This is attributable to the pathetic condition of their workshops, the leakages on the porous roofs end up “brutally” damaging the clay idols & their spirit.
 
 However, when the prayers were not answered in the year 2021, I decided to venture into this iconic spot with the aim to document those moments of struggle.

Sheet1.Title: Caught in the moment
Sheet1.Description:
I framed this moment at the ghats of Varanasi, India. The sheer joy and happiness of these children playing in the holy waters of River Ganges filled me up with positive energy. They were carefree and were living the moment, which most of us fail to do. We are so burdened with our own desires, expectations and responsibilities that we forget to live in the present and always think about what future holds for us. 
 I am so glad that I could capture the moment which lasted split seconds.

Sheet1.Title: Guided By Faith
Sheet1.Description:
It is believed that to one who has faith, no explanation is necessary and to one without any, no explanation is possible. India, the land of diversity in its rich heritage, culture, religion, geographical distributions and what not, is divided by many elements but united by the power of faith. An intense five letter word in the Indian subcontinent finds its significance in the hearts of people irrespective of their backgrounds.
 
 A man in the said image takes a holy dip in the Yamuna River, on an early foggy winter morning before getting on with his day where his faith will drive away any difficulties that he might encounter.
 
 Coming under one umbrella that unites people can be tough in a diverse land but a mind that believes in moving past all distractions from getting divided is joined by the power of belief and faith.

Sheet1.Title: polar prowl
Sheet1.Description:
A large Polar Bear (Ursus maritimus) scans the tundra for food in the outskirts of Churchill, Manitoba, Canada. In the waning weeks of October, Hudson Bay, the largest body of water in the Canadian subarctic starts to freeze. In a few more weeks, these ice bears--the largest land predator--will be able to go on the sea ice to hunt ice seals. 
 
 But before all that, these bears have to make do with what they can feed on on land. Seaweed, berries, injured animals--anything is fair game. With tens of other bears converging in this area to wait for the freeze, the competition for prey has increased exponentially. The hunt is afoot.

Sheet1.Title: The Protector
Sheet1.Description:
Cheetahs. 
 
 The fastest animal in the world. In less than 3 seconds, it will go from 0 to 100 and 100 to 0. What does it take to accomplish such a remarkable feat? Evolutionary engineering under the direction of the world's top engineer, Nature. 
 
 It has large traction pads on its feet and a long tail that serves as a rudder to steer, stabilize, and balance. Non-retractable claws, like a soccer player's cleats, are an adaptation to assist retain traction. Daytime hunting requires distinct black "tear tracks" flowing from the inside corner of each eye to the mouth as an anti-glare technique.

Sheet1.Title: Day of the fisher!
Sheet1.Description:
Spending even a few minutes amidst nature can be a learning experience for anyone, I believe. We just need to be patient and carefully observe the things happening around us. I came across this beautiful Common Kingfisher, during one of my visits to Bharatpur National Park in India and was lucky to witness its hunting behaviour. After a couple of failed attempts, it was finally able to catch a fish. I was sitting quite close to it and was able to take a couple of images with nice details. 
 The determination of the bird taught me how important it is to never give up and how strong the power of patience, dedication and perseverance can be. Moments like these and many more in Nature are always trying to convey vital life lessons for us all, because no matter what, we all are connected in this circle of life. From an ant to an elephant, the struggle for survival is evident across all forms of life on Earth.

Sheet1.Title: In-sync
Sheet1.Description:
One of the best periods of my life was working as an intern at Agumbe Rainforest Research Station, where I was part of the King Cobra Ecology and Conservation project. During one of my days in the field, I was resting in my hammock when it suddenly started to rain. I decided to go shoot some birds which I could hear calling in the neighbouring paddy field, since it was starting to fill up due to the heavy downpour. This collected water acted as a hotspot for many birds and thus using it to my advantage I started taking some photographs. I viewed my recent captures as soon as I called time, and this photograph caught my eye; it seemed as if one of the Ibises was shadowing the movements of the other and that too under the rain! I can never forget this beautiful moment I was a witness to!

 Location: Agumbe, Karnataka, India

Often ignored in wildlife photography, the spotted deers horns make a beautiful subject. It was a misty morning and we set out to find a tiger family. It was a cold winter morning.
 
 After an hour into the drive we stopped to have some coffee. I kept looking at the scenery and right next to me out of no where these horns popped out. This beautiful deer popped out of the grass curiously looking and smelling whatever we were having. I managed to take this shot then.

Sheet1.Title: Fragile future
Sheet1.Description:
Cheetah cubs have the highest mortality rate among other big cat cubs. It’s the toughest job for a cheetah mom to make sure her litter stays alive. Their population is deteriorating at an alarming rate and cheetahs are at the verge extinction.
 
 In a dainty little park called Rietvlei nature reserve, there is a female cheetah known as “Sahara”. Against all the odds she was able to raise 6 cubs to an age of 1 year. This is a miraculous feat for any big cat. 
 
 In frame is one of the cubs looking forward for a brighter future even though it looks fragile.

Sheet1.Title: FERRYMAN BETWIXT THE MERGING

However, in my case, I feel the need and the joy to express myself through my work and I put it out there for the others to see and experience in their own way. My photography celebrates possibility: by showing the vastness of space, my work shows and celebrates our opportunity to grow, explore and embrace the unexpected. While the average individual may simply be interested in how soothing a picture is to the eyes, a photographic artist may be looking at the composition of the picture, the use of colors and light, and any additional meanings conveyed by the picture. Humans tend to organize the disorderly world in an intelligible way, but sometimes we reverse the process in an attempt to disintegrate the world order into disorder. Does the world have an order? What is the relation between art and reality? Th

Sheet1.Title: Dream Walk

It's exciting to see the world we don't see in infrared photos. The human eye can see between 400 and 600 nanometers. We can see from 600 nanometers with infrared filters. But what we see is unorthodox. The green leaves of the trees are white. The water and the sky turn darker. These images make me feel like I'm dreaming.
 This photo was taken on a sunny day in the Bursa Botanical Park on a day of walking, with a camera with 720 nanometers of infrared filter. That's why I called it the Dream walk.

This picture of a local Shikara rider going back to his home after a dull day in an otherwise crowded empty touristy lake, shows hope & belief for a better dawn the next day, a better season after two years of struggle.

Sheet1.Title: Ruins of the Great Temple
Sheet1.Description:
Three novices with umbrellas step down the old stairway of Mingun Pahtowdawgyi after observing the giant cracks along the face of the stupa due to earthquake in 1839.
 Mingun Pahtowdawgyi was intentionally uncompleted with a height of 162 feet and with girth about 450 square feet since King Bodawpaya in Kongbaung period (1790). King Bodawpaya was a superstitious man and during the construction, it was prophesied that the completion of the great stupa would cause his death or the destruction of the country. Worried about maintaining his empire, the king slowed progress on the stupa. When he died, construction was abandoned completely.
 Mingun Pahtowdawgyi is located in Mingun, Sagaing Division, Myanmar.

Sheet1.Title: The Sea Angel
Sheet1.Description:
We are a Marine Life Conservation Organization. All income goes towards our Marine conservation and Protection Projects.
 
 A few Facts about Manta Rays
 
 The word ‘manta’ is actually Spanish for blanket or cloak, and it’s pretty easy to see the connection.
 Manta rays have the largest brain to body weight ratio of any living fish; giving it enough cleverness to make the average dolphin jealous.
 A fully grown oceanic manta ray can reach a wing span of up to 7 meters and weigh up to two tonnes.
 Manta Rays are listed as vulnerable by the International Union for Conservation of Nature. Anthropogenic threats include pollution, entanglement in fishing nets, and direct harvesting for their gill rakers for use in Chinese medicine.
 
 Their slow reproductive rate exacerbates these threats. They are protected in international waters by the Convention on Migratory Species of Wild Animals, but are more vulnerable closer to shore.
 We are protecting these gorgeous Sea Angels!
